#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md:37
msgid "Allocation Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md:39
msgid ""
"Three methods are available to derive an assignment from the importance "
"matrix and the per-party constituency counts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid "Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid "`OPTIMAL` *(default)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid ""
"Hungarian algorithm (Kuhn-Munkres). Finds the assignment that provably "
"maximises the total importance score. More computationally intensive, but"
" globally optimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid "`GREEDY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid ""
"Iteratively assigns the (constituency, party) pair with the highest "
"importance, as long as the party's quota has not yet been exhausted. "
"Fast, but not globally optimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid "`STABLE_MATCHING`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md
msgid ""
"Gale-Shapley algorithm (stable matching). No constituency-party pair "
"would simultaneously prefer a different assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md:49
msgid "Effect of `constituency_representation`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md:51
msgid ""
"**`ENTIRE_PARLIAMENT`** *(default)*: Importance is computed from the "
"votes of all parties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/constituency_assignment.md:52
msgid ""
"**`GOVERNING_MAJORITY`**: Only the votes of the governing parties are "
"used to compute importance."
msgstr ""

